<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINE, CUMMINS ISM -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Accelerator Pedal TPS/IVS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Accelerator Pedal TPS/IVS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The following four tests check the throttle position sensor (TPS), the idle validation switch (IVS)
                and the related International cab and engine harness circuits connected to the ECM.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following four tests must be performed in sequence.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>The tests should be performed if a Cummins fault code indicates a problem in the circuits or if the
                Compulink, EZ-Tech or Pro-Link 9000 EST indicates that the TPS/IVS is not working properly while
                monitoring switches. If Compulink&#8482; detects a fault with the IVS circuits while monitoring
                switches, the display would show Idle Validation Switch = Fault. If a fault is present while monitoring
                Percent Of Throttle, the percent displayed does not indicate actual throttle position.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following two tests,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="x0823602">Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="x0823603">Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</hotlnk>, check operation of the
                        TPS and IVS, but do not check the timing between the two functions.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823602">
            <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)</title>
            <para>This test checks the TPS circuits in the accelerator pedal assembly. This test will help identify if
                the resistances are within specifications and if there are any opens or shorts in the TPS, but
                <emph type="bold">will not</emph>verify the correct switching of the IVS and TPS.
            </para>
            <table id="t0823602" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.65in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.99in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.52in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect accelerator pedal from cab harness at connector (309). At pedal side of
                                    (309) measure resistance between terminals B and C with the pedal in the idle
                                    position, then with the pedal fully depressed.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS, B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2000 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With the pedal in the idle position, at pedal, measure resistance between
                                    terminals A and C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS A to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1500 to 3000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With the pedal in the full throttle position, at pedal, measure resistance between
                                    terminals B and C. Is reading 1000 ohms less than reading at idle position and
                                    between 250 and 1500 ohms?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS, B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>250 to 1500 ohms, and &#60; idle position reading -1000 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At the accelerator pedal, measure resistance between gnd. (metal part of pedal)
                                    and terminals A, B, C, D, and E.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS, A, B, C, D, and E to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The TPS sensor checks good. Proceed to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0823603">Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</hotlnk>
                                    which checks the idle validation portion of the accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823603">
            <title>Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</title>
            <para>This test checks the IVS circuits in the accelerator pedal assembly.</para>
            <para>Perform
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0823602">Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS)</hotlnk>before performing this test.
            </para>
            <table id="t0823603" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.48in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect accelerator pedal from cab harness at conn. (309). At pedal side of
                                    (309) measure resistance between terminals F and E with pedal in idle position. Is
                                    it &#60;125 ohms?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS/ IVS, F to E.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>125 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At pedal measure resistance between terminals F and E while slowly depressing the
                                    pedal (idle to full throttle). After approximately 10 degrees of travel, is the
                                    resistance 100K ohms or more?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS/ IVS, F to E.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At pedal measure resistance between terminals F and D while the pedal is at idle
                                    position.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS/ IVS, F to D.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At pedal measure resistance between terminals F and D while slowly depressing the
                                    pedal (idle to full throttle). After approximately 10 degrees of travel the
                                    resistance should be less than 125 ohms.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS/ IVS, F to D.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;125 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At pedal measure resistance between metal part of accelerator pedal and terminals
                                    D, E and F.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>TPS/ IVS, metal to D, E, and F.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the TPS/IVS switch, then recalibrate (refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The TPS/IVS pedal assembly checks good. Note that this test is not able to check
                                    the timing between TPS and IVS functions.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823604">
            <title>Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) System for "Short or Open" Circuits</title>
            <para>This test checks the cab and engine harness TPS/IVS circuits for opens, shorts to ground, shorts to
                "hot" circuits and shorts to other circuits in the harness.
            </para>
            <para>Perform the two preceding tests,
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0823602">Testing Throttle Position Sensor</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0823603">Testing Idle Validation Switch (IVS</hotlnk>), before performing this test.
            </para>
            <table id="t0823604" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Accelerator Pedal (TPS/IVS) System for "Short or Open" Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.83in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.47in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With (309) disconnected, disconnect connector (1091) from ECM and inspect ECM
                                    connector. Connector and ECM pins OK?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace connector terminals if damaged. If ECM pins are damaged, have Cummins
                                    dealer replace ECM. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>to recalibrate the ECM
                                    to TPS/IVS.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test leads and measure resistance to gnd. at terminals 3,
                                    13, 49, 47, 48 and 10 (circuits 99B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A and 99-G). Do not use
                                    probes or leads other than Cummins P/N 3822758 or the connector could be damaged.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(1091), 99B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A and 99-G to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit where terminal resistance is less than 100K
                                    ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test leads and measure resistance between terminals 3, 13,
                                    49, 47, 48 and 10 (circuits 99B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A and 99-G) and all other
                                    terminals in (1091).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(1091), between 99B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A, and 99-G and all other circuits in
                                    conn.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short between any circuits where resistance between terminals is less than
                                    100K ohms, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test leads and measure voltage to gnd. at terminals 3, 13,
                                    49, 47, 48 and 10 (circuits 98B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A and 99-G).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(252), 99B, 99C, 97-GA, 99, 99A and 99-G to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0823606">Testing TPS/ IVS Circuits for Continuity.</hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to unwanted voltage source in any circuit where more than 1.5 volts
                                    is present, then repair. Go to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ECM Calibration</hotlnk>to recalibrate ECM/
                                    accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823606">
            <title>Testing TPS/IVS Circuits for Continuity</title>
            <para>This test checks the individual TPS and IVS circuits (cab and engine harness) for correct
                <emph type="bold">resistance</emph>
                while disconnected from the accelerator pedal assembly and ECM.
                <emph type="bold">Perform the preceding three tests before performing this test.</emph>
            </para>
            <table id="t0823605" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing TPS/IVS Circuits for Continuity</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.68in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At ECM connector (1091) use test lead to jumper terminal 47 to 48 (circuit 99 to
                                    99A). At conn. (309) measure resistance between terminals A and B (cir. 99 to 99A).
                                    Do not use probes or leads other than Cummins P/N 3822758 or the ECM connector could
                                    be damaged.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), 99 to 99A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of out-of- specification resistance in either circuit 99 or 99A(5V),
                                    then repair. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test lead to jumper terminal 47 to 49 (cir. 99 to 99-G).
                                    At connector (309) measure resistance between terminals A and B (cir. 99-G to 99).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), 99-G to 99.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of out-of- specification resistance in circuit 99-G, then repair.
                                    Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test lead to jumper terminal 47 to 3 (cir. 99 to 99C). At
                                    connector (309) measure resistance between terminals A and E (cir. 99 to 99C).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), 99 to 99C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of out-of- specification resistance in circuit 99C, then repair.
                                    Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test lead to jumper terminal 47 to 13 (cir. 99 to 99B). At
                                    connector (309) measure resistance between terminals A and D (cir. 99 to 99B).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), 99 to 99B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of out-of- specification resistance in circuit 99B, then repair.
                                    Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Recalibration</hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (1091) use test lead to jumper terminal 47 to 10 (cir. 99 to 97-GA).
                                    At connector (309) measure resistance between terminals A and F (cir. 99 to 99-GA).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(309), 99 to 99-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of out-of- specification resistance in circuit 99-GA or 97-GA, then
                                    repair. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0820005">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration</hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If the preceding three, and this test, have been performed and defects were not
                                    noted, the TPS and IVS circuits check good. If the problem is still present, replace
                                    the accelerator pedal. If this does not correct the problem, have Cummins dealer
                                    diagnose the ECM operation.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0820005">
            <title>Accelerator/ECM Calibration</title>
            <para>The electronic accelerator pedal assembly and the ECM must be calibrated when:</para>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>The pedal assembly is initially installed.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The pedal assembly or sensor is replaced.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The accelerator pedal is disconnected (at any point in the circuitry) and the key switch is
                        placed in the on position.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>To recalibrate the accelerator pedal and ECM:</para>
            <seqlist style="alphauc">
                <item>
                    <para>The vehicle key must be in the on position.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Depress the accelerator pedal slowly through the complete range of movement, then release.
                        Slowly depress and release, three times in this manner. This completes the calibration process.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
